# Enterprise Architecture (FFLib)

## Required Layers

All features must follow Domain-Service-Selector-UnitOfWork pattern.

### Triggers → Domain
```apex
trigger AccountTrigger on Account (...) {
    fflib_SObjectDomain.triggerHandler(Accounts.class);
}
```

### Domain (validation + field defaults)
- Plural object name: `Accounts`, `Opportunities`
- Extends `fflib_SObjectDomain`
- Inner `Constructor` class implementing `IConstructable`

### Selector (all SOQL)
- `AccountsSelector extends fflib_SObjectSelector`
- Never write inline SOQL outside selectors
- Use `newQueryFactory()` for dynamic queries

### Service (business logic + orchestration)
- `AccountService` implements `IAccountService`
- Only layer that uses Unit of Work for DML

### Application Factory
- Register all bindings in `Application.cls`
- UnitOfWork, Selector, Domain, Service factories

## Testing with FFLib
- Use `fflib_ApexMocks` for layer isolation
- Mock selectors, UoW, and services via `Application.*.setMock()`
- Use `Application.UnitOfWork.newInstance()` for test data DML — not TestDataGraph

## Logging
- Use NebulaLogger instead of `System.debug()` — `Logger.info()`, `Logger.error()`, etc.
- Always call `Logger.saveLog()` to persist
- Use `.addTag('FeatureName')` for log categorization
- Reference `references/NebulaLogger/` for patterns

## References
- `references/fflib-apex-common/` for base classes
- `references/fflib-apex-mocks/` for test mocking
- `references/NebulaLogger/` for logging patterns

## Async
- Async classes delegate to Service methods — no direct SOQL/DML
- Enqueue from Services or Domains, never from Selectors

## LWC
- Controllers are thin wrappers — one-line delegation to Service or Selector
- Read operations (`cacheable=true`) call Selectors directly
- Write operations call Service methods
- Never put business logic in the controller
- Reference `references/lwc-patterns.md` for full patterns

## Configuration
- Access CMDTs through dedicated selectors (e.g., `AppConfigSelector`) registered in `Application.cls`
- Use `newInstance()` factory pattern — keeps config mockable in tests
- Template: `AppConfigSelector.cls` in `templates/salesforce/classes/enterprise/`
- One selector per CMDT domain (config, feature flags, integrations, mappings)
- Never query CMDTs inline — always go through a selector

## Rules
- No SOQL outside Selectors
- No DML outside Unit of Work — including test setup
- No inline CMDT queries — use config selectors
- Business logic in Services, not Domains
- Don't skip Service layer for "simple" operations
- Don't use lightweight TriggerHandler - use fflib_SObjectDomain
